    <section>
        <h2>Position 1: Front-End Developer</h2>
        <p><strong>Reference Number:</strong> DEV123</p>
        <p><strong>Position Title:</strong> Front-End Developer</p>
        <p><strong>Brief Description:</strong> We are looking for a passionate Front-End Developer to join our growing web
            development team. The role will involve developing user-facing features for our web applications using modern
            technologies.</p>
        <p><strong>Salary Range:</strong> $60,000 - $80,000 per annum</p>
        <p><strong>Reports To:</strong> Lead Web Developer</p>

        <h3>Key Responsibilities</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Develop new user-facing features with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript</li>
            <li>Ensure the technical feasibility of UI/UX designs</li>
            <li>Collaborate with back-end developers and web designers to improve usability</li>
            <li>Optimize applications for maximum speed and scalability</li>
            <li>Maintain and improve website</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Required Qualifications, Skills, and Knowledge</h3>
        <h4>Essential</h4>
        <ul>
            <li>Proficiency in HTML, CSS, and JavaScript</li>
            <li>Experience with front-end frameworks like React or Angular</li>
            <li>Strong understanding of responsive design principles</li>
            <li>At least 2 years of experience in web development</li>
        </ul>

        <h4>Preferable</h4>
        <ul>
            <li>Experience with version control systems such as Git</li>
            <li>Familiarity with CSS preprocessors like SASS or LESS</li>
            <li>Basic understanding of back-end technologies like Node.js</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Position 2: IT Systems Architect</h2>
        <p><strong>Reference Number:</strong> SYS456</p>
        <p><strong>Position Title:</strong> IT Systems Architect</p>
        <p><strong>Brief Description:</strong> We are seeking an experienced IT Systems Architect to design and implement
            complex IT solutions for large-scale projects. This role will involve defining system architecture, ensuring
            scalability, and overseeing infrastructure implementation.</p>
        <p><strong>Salary Range:</strong> $100,000 - $120,000 per annum</p>
        <p><strong>Reports To:</strong> Chief Technology Officer (CTO)</p>

        <h3>Key Responsibilities</h3>
        <ol>
            <li>Design system architectures for large-scale IT solutions</li>
            <li>Assess and optimize existing systems for efficiency and scalability</li>
            <li>Provide technical guidance to software development teams</li>
            <li>Collaborate with stakeholders to understand project requirements</li>
            <li>Ensure systems are secure and compliant with industry standards</li>
        </ol>

        <h3>Required Qualifications, Skills, and Knowledge</h3>
        <h4>Essential</h4>
        <ul>
            <li>Proven experience as an IT Systems Architect or similar role</li>
            <li>Strong knowledge of cloud computing platforms (AWS, Azure, etc.)</li>
            <li>Experience with system design, network architecture, and software development</li>
            <li>Minimum 5 years of experience in IT systems architecture</li>
            <li>Strong communication and leadership skills</li>
        </ul>

        <h4>Preferable</h4>
        <ul>
            <li>Certification in AWS or Azure cloud platforms</li>
            <li>Familiarity with DevOps practices</li>
            <li>Experience with microservices architecture</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

